0crisis%2C%20after%20a%20recent%20political%20standoff%20over%20the%20government's%20borrowing%20limit%20fueled%20fears%20of%20a%20sovereign%20default.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20an%20eleventh-hour%20political%20deal%20averted%20a%20payment%20default%20in%20early%20June%2C%20the%20Treasury%20has%20already%20borrowed%20more%20than%20%241%20trillion%20%E2%80%93%20bringing%20its%20total%20tab%20to%20almost%20%2433%20trillion.%20This%20astronomical%20figure%20has%20worried%20many%20Americans%3A%20high-profile%20investor%20Ray%20Dalio%20warned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fray-dalio-us-debt-crisis-economy-recession-outlook-borrowing-ceiling-2023-6%5C%22%3Enation%20is%20at%20the%20start%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Blate%2C%20big%20cycle%20debt%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Fisher%20himself%20is%20much%20more%20relaxed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DazRTCiHwW_E%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpeaking%20in%20a%20recent%20Youtube%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Fisher%20Investments%20stressed%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20borrowings%20%E2%80%93%20relative%20to%20the%20size%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20country's%20ability%20to%20afford%20the%20obligations%20%E2%80%93%20is%20what%20really%20matters%2C%20and%20not%20the%20overall%20level%20of%20debt%20itself.%20Currently%2C%20that%20metric%20is%20at%20moderate%20levels%20similar%20to%20those%20seen%20in%201980%20or%20even%20as%20far%20back%20as%201950%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%201989%20to%202000%2C%20we%20were%20much%20higher%20than%20we%20are%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20carrying%20cost%20of%20US%20government%20debt.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20could%20carry%20it%20then%2C%20we%20can%20carry%20it%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20US%20avoided%20a%20payment%20default%20on