%20Territories%20which%20missed%20the%20deadline%20to%20sanction%20them%20and%20allocated%20them%20to%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20which%20had%20sought%20additional%20resources%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fdeadline-missed-23-states-uts-lose-1-44-lakh-pmay-units-to-up-8844828%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development%2C%20which%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Awas%20Yojana-Gramin%20(PMAY-G)%20scheme%2C%20has%20conveyed%20this%20to%20the%20states%20and%20UTs%20where%20the%20allocation%20of%20houses%20has%20been%20revised%20downwards%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20set%20a%20target%20of%20constructing%202.95%20crore%20houses%20under%20the%20PMAY-G%20scheme%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20by%20March%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.04%20crore%20houses%20from%20the%20total%20were%20allocated%20to%20states%20based%20on%20the%20Socio-Economic%20Caste%20Census%20(SECC)%20data.%20The%20remaining%2091%20lakh%20houses%20were%20allocated%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1906802%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAwaas%3C%2Fem%3E%2B%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20the%20government%20in%20January%2C%202018%20to%20March%2C%202019%20to%20identify%20those%20beneficiaries%20which%20claimed%20to%20have%20been%20left%20out%20under%20the%202011%20SECC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fpm-awas-yojana-problems%5C%22%3ESix%20Years%20On%20And%20Despite%20The%20Praise%2C%20The%20PM%20Awas%20Yojana%20Is%20Still%20Riddled%20With%20Faults%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20two%20dozen%20states%20and%20UTs%20together%20failed%20to%20sanction%20a%20total%20of%201%2C44%2C220%20houses%20%E2%80%93%207%2C496%20from%20SECC%20data%20and%201%2C36%2C724%20from%20the%20Awaas%2B%20list%20%E2%80%93%20before%20the%20deadline%20of%20June%2030%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20states%20and%20UTs%20are%3A%20Gujarat%2C%20Tripura%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Sikkim%2C%20Meghalaya%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Assam%2C%20Nagaland%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Ladakh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20was%20initially%20allocated%2034.72%20lakh%20houses%2C%20had%20sought%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20approval%20for%20additional%20houses.%20The%20state%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20chief%20minister%2C%20Keshav%20Prasad%20Maurya%2C%20who%20holds%20the%20rural%20development%20portfolio%2C%20had%20written%20to%20Union%20rural%20development%20minister%20Giriraj%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20confirming%20receipt%20of%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20regarding%20the%20additional%20allocation%2C%20Maurya%20has%20said%20that%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20would%20need%2095%2C000%20more%20houses%20to%20ensure%20housing%20for%20all%20eligible%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689667884000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F01140522%2FWhatsApp-Image-2022-03-01-at-13.26.17.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fover-1-lakh-houses-under-pmay-g-diverted-to-up-after-24-states-and-uts-fail-to-sanction-them%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20government%20has%20set%20a%20target%20of%20constructing%202.95%20crore%20houses%20under%20the%20PMAY-G%20scheme%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20by%20March%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A