aluru%2C%20Here%20Are%20the%209%20Big%20Factors%20at%20Play%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132549%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.04.45-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Opposition%20leaders%20of%2026%20political%20parties%20are%20all%20set%20to%20formalise%20the%20shape%20of%20a%20united%20front%20against%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20on%20July%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20summit%20at%20the%20Taj%20West%20End%20in%20Bengaluru%20is%20the%20second%20such%20meeting%20of%20opposition%20parties%2C%20after%20initial%20discussions%20were%20held%20between%20the%20parties%20in%20Patna%20on%20June%2023.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20opposition%20front%20has%20already%20got%20a%20shot%20up%2C%20with%20all%20of%20them%20agreeing%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20forging%20an%20ideological%20and%20issue-based%20alliance%20against%20the%20BJP%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20The%20number%20of%20participating%20parties%20has%20also%20increased%20from%2017%20in%20Patna%20to%2026%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20some%20of%20these%20parties%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20together%20in%20a%20few%20states%20like%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Kerala%20has%20not%20deterred%20the%20leaders%20from%20finding%20common%20ground%20as%20far%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20pitch%20is%20concerned.%20The%20opposition%20leaders%20have%20agreed%20to%20showcase%20their%20unity%20in%20the%20upcoming%20monsoon%20session%20of%20the%20Parliament%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20draw%20up%20a%20common%20agenda%20to%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%2C%20too%2C%20has%20suddenly%20decided%20to%20hold%20a%20meeting%20in%20Delhi%20on%20July%2018%20with%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%E2%80%99s%20constituents.%20However%2C%20its%20former%20allies%20like%20the%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20and%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(Badal)%20are%20still%20non-committal%20about%20joining%20the%20NDA.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20meeting%20will%20most%20likely%20be%20dominated%20by%20the%20BJP.%20Although%20the%20BJP%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20meeting%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20attended%20by%2038%20parties%2C%20most%20of%20the%20current%20NDA%20constituents%20are%20small%20caste-based%20outfits%20in%20different%20states%2C%20regional%20parties%20in%20the%20north-eastern%20states%2C%20and%20factional%20groups%20that%20have%20emerged%20from%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20meetings%20go%20on%20today%2C%20here%20are%20the%20nine%20major%20factors%20at%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20The%20opposition%20meeting%20is%20an%20unprecedented%20effort%20by%20leaders%20of%20influential%20regional%20and%20national%20political%20parties%20to%20come%20together%20against%20what%20they%20allege%20is%20growing%20authoritarianism%2C%20political%20takeover%20of%20institutions%2C%20misuse%20of%20central%20investigation%20agencies%20against%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20and%20issues%20like%20price%20rise%2C%20corruption%20and%20unemployment%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Unlike%20a%20similar%20effort%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20opposition%20forces%20have%20focused%20heavily%20on%20striking%20a%20rapport%20between%20different%20parties%20while%20trying%20to%20iron%20out%20the%20differences%20much%20before%20the%20actual%20campaign%20kicks%20off.%20The%20tagline%20for%20the%20front%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9CUnited%20We%20Stand%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20has%20been%20highlighted%20in%20posters%20and%20banners%20across%20the%20streets%20of%20Bengaluru%20ahead%20of%20the%20opposition%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132658%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.08.20-PM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132658%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.08.20-PM.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132658%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.08.20-PM-300x180.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663755%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22613%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOpposition%20leaders%20in%20Bengaluru%20on%20Tuesday.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Some%20reports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Foppn-meet-bengaluru-tuesday-common-name-agenda-cong-admits-will-take-time-8844555%2F%5C%22%3Eindicated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20opposition%20parties%20will%20decide%20on%20having%20a%20central%20secretariat%20for%20the%20united%20front%20to%20coordinate%20between%20different%20parties.%20The%20secretariat%20will%20have%20a%20convenor%20and%20a%20president%2C%20likely%20to%20be%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20and%20former%20Congress%20president%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20respectively.%20The%20secretariat%20will%20spell%20out%20a%20common%20agenda%2C%20plan%20campaign%20strategies%2C%20joint%20rallies%20and%20programmes%2C%20and%20strive%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20consensual%20seat-sharing%20formula%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20Leaders%20are%20also%20likely%20to%20finalise%20a%20name%20for%20the%20opposition%20front%20in%20Bengaluru.%20Sources%20told%20The%20Wire%20that%20the%20name%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20INDIA%20%E2%80%93%20Indian%20National%20Democratic%20Inclusive%20Alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20leaders%20also%20believe%20that%20they%20should%20discuss%20the%20limitations%20of%20EVM%20and%20raise%20some%20of%20their%20concerns%20with%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20and%20suggest%20a%20few%20reforms%20in%20the%20election%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20leaders%20have%20agreed%20to%20have%20a%20common%20minimum%20agenda%20designed%20around%20%E2%80%9Csafeguarding%20democracy%2C%20Constitution%2C%20and%20secularism%E2%80%9D%20and%20livelihood%20issues%20like%20inflation%20and%20unemployment.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fbengaluru-opposition-meet-live-updates-congress-aap-shiv-sena-ncp-8842961%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%3A%20%E2%80%9CBroadly%20the%20agenda%20comprises%20six%20proposals%20%E2%80%94%20setting%20up%20separate%20subcommittees%20for%20drafting%20a%20common%20agenda%20and%20communication%20points%20for%20the%20alliance%20for%20the%202024%20general%20elections%3B%20chalking%20out%20a%20joint%20programme%20for%20parties%2C%20including%20rallies%2C%20conventions%20and%20agitations%3B%20deciding%20seat-sharing%20on%20a%20state%20to%20state%20basis%3B%20suggesting%20a%20name%20for%20the%20alliance%3B%20setting%20up%20a%20common%20secretariat%20for%20it%3B%20and%20discussing%20EVMs%20and%20suggesting%20reforms%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20The%20opposition%20summit%20got%20a%20boost%20after%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20decided%20to%20join%20it%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20after%20the%20Congress%20declared%20its%20unequivocal%20opposition%20to%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20ordinance%20to%20wrest%20control%20of%20the%20bureaucracy%20from%20the%20Delhi%20government.%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20who%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20bringing%20all%20the%20opposition%20parties%20together%2C%20reportedly%20convinced%20the%20Congress%20leaders%20to%20take%20a%20stand%20on%20the%20issue%20ahead%20of%20the%20Bengaluru%20meeting.%20Although%20the%20Congress%20had%20initially%20opposed%20the%20ordinance%2C%20its%20Punjab%20and%20Delhi%20units%20were%20opposed%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20unconditional%20support%20to%20its%20primary%20rival%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENCP%20supremo%20Sharad%20Pawar%20also%20created%20a%20flutter%20ahead%20of%20the%20meeting%20by%20remaining%20conspicuously%20absent%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20his%20position.%20But%20he%20soon%20cleared%20the%20air%20by%20announcing%20that%20he%20will%20join%20the%20meeting%20on%20July%2018.%20Congress%20general%20secretary%20(organisation)%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20said%20that%20more%20parties%20are%20likely%20to%20join%20the%20front%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132719%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.05.00-PM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132719%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.05.00-PM.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132719%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.05.00-PM-300x180.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132719%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.05.00-PM-1024x614.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663756%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOpposition%20leaders%20in%20Bengaluru%20on%20Tuesday.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20The%20meeting%20informally%20kicked%20off%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20July%2017%20when%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20leaders%20met%20for%20a%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20Karnataka%20chief%20minister%20Siddaramaiah.%20Leaders%20showed%20an%20unusual%20bonhomie%20during%20the%20dinner.%20All%20top%20leaders%20including%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%2C%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20Sitaram%20Yechury%2C%20D.Raja%2C%20M.K.Stalin%2C%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20and%20others%20were%20present%20at%20the%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E9.%20The%2026%20parties%20participating%20in%20the%20summit%20are%20Congress%2C%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2C%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%2C%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%2C%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20%E2%80%93%20Sharad%20Pawar%20faction%2C%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal%2C%20Apna%20Dal%20(Kamerawadi)%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20National%20Conference%2C%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist-Leninist)%20Liberation%2C%20Revolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%2C%20All%20India%20Forward%20Bloc%2C%20Marumalarchi%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20Viduthalai%20Chiruthaigal%20Katchi%2C%20Kongunadu%20Makkal%20Desia%2C%20Manithaneya%20Makkal%20Katchi%2C%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%2C%20Kerala%20Congress%20(M)%20and%20Kerala%20Congress%20(Joseph).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20front%20has%20kept%20some%20key%20players%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20and%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20%E2%80%93%20who%20have%20been%20opposed%20to%20the%20BJP%20out%20of%20the%20grouping%20because%20of%20a%20direct%20conflict%20with%20some%20of%20the%20more%20important%20constituents%20of%20the%20opposition%20front%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689667153000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18132549%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-18-at-1.04.45-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-opposition-parties-meet-in-bengaluru-here-are-the-9-big-factors-at-play%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fact%20that%20some%20of%20these%20parties%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20together%20in%20a%20few%20states%20like%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Kerala%20has%20not%20deterred%20the%20leaders%20from%20finding%20common%20ground%20as%20far%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20pitch%20is%20concerned.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-opposition-parties-meet-in-bengaluru-here-are-the-9-big-factors-at-play%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Zhou%20Xun%2C%20Jelly%20Lin%20Head%20the%20Cast%20of%20Chinese%20Sexual%20Assault%20Drama%20%E2%80%98Imperfect%20Victim%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689666595000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FZhou-Xun-in-Imperfect-Victim-Unit-Still-01EN-Courtesy-of-iQIYI-cr-res.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235672826%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Movie%20stars%20Zhou%20Xun%20and%20Jelly%20Lin%20head%20the%20cast%20of%20%E2%80%9CImperfect%20Victim%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20new%20mainland%20Chinese%20drama%20series%20that%20focuses%20on%20workplace%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20leads%20to%20a%20rape%20trial.%20Zhou%20(%E2%80%9CCloud%20Atlas%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Silent%20War%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CPainted%20Skin%E2%80%9D)%20plays%20a%20lawyer%20who%20steps%20in%20to%20represent%20the%20character%20played%20by%20Lin%20(%E2%80%9CThe%20Mermaid%E2%80%9D)%2C%20who%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Patrick%20Frater%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fzhou-xun-jelly-lin-sexual-assault-drama-imperfect-victim-1235672826%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fzhou-xun-jelly-lin-sexual-assault-drama-imperfect-victim-1235672826%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fzhou-xun-jelly-lin-sexual-assault-drama-imperfect-victim-1235672826%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20China%20to%20AI%3A%20How%20India%20Voted%20at%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Human%20Rights%20Body%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFrom%20China%E2%80%99s%20oldest%20recurring%20resolution%20to%20bringing%20human%20rights%20into%20the%20realm%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%2C%20India%20has%20had%20to%20make%20some%20policy%20adjustments%20at%20the%20recently%20concluded%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20which%20continue%20to%20signal%20its%20current%20geo-political%20and%20domestic%20policy%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%E2%80%99s%20human%20rights%20body%2C%20based%20in%20Geneva%2C%20holds%20three%20regular%20sessions%20during%20a%20year.%20The%20mid-summer%20session%20ended%20on%20Friday%2C%20passing%2030%20resolutions%20%E2%80%93%20a%20majority%20of%20which%20were%20adopted%20without%20a%20vote%20or%20a%20consensus.%20However%2C%20two%20of%20these%20resolutions%20which%20were%20adopted%20without%20a%20vote%2C%20however%2C%20had%20to%20face%20amendments%20from%20several%20countries%20that%20were%20rejected%20by%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%20ten%20UNHRC%20resolutions%20that%20were%20put%20to%20a%20ballot%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20five%20times%2C%20abstained%20four%20times%2C%20and%20opposed%20one%20resolution.%20Additionally%2C%20India%20issued%20six%20statements%20regarding%20the%20adopted%20resolutions%2C%20with%20only%20one%20statement%20providing%20an%20explanation%20for%20its%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20look%20at%20the%20notable%20signals%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20voting%20pattern%20in%20the%2053rd%20UNHRC%20session%20that%20ended%20on%20July%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20change%20in%20its%20position%20on%20a%20China-sponsored%20resolution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20sole%20Explanation%20of%20Vote%20was%20on%20a%20resolution%20tabled%20by%20China%20on%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.26%2FEnglish_2.doc%5C%22%3EContribution%20of%20Development%20to%20the%20Enjoyment%20of%20All%20Human%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20which%20was%20passed%20by%2030%20votes%20in%20favour%2C%20five%20abstentions%20and%2012%20votes%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Western%20nations%2C%20led%20by%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20EU%2C%20voted%20en%20bloc%20against%20the%20resolution%2C%20while%20India%2C%20Paraguay%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Chile%20and%20Costa%20Rica%20abstained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20explanation%20of%20vote%20statement%2C%20India%20said%20that%20it%20had%20made%20proposals%20for%20amendments%20%E2%80%9Crelated%20to%20the%20terms%20and%20concepts%20that%20are%20not%20universally%20accepted%20and%20we%20believe%20that%20they%20should%20have%20been%20taken%20on%20board%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20continue%20to%20have%20reservations%20on%20use%20of%20such%20terms%20and%20concepts%20in%20the%20text%20instead%20of%20already%20agreed%20language%20within%20the%20SDG%20Framework%2C%20India%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmindiaun.gov.in%2Fpageinfo%2FMzAxNg%2C%2C%5C%22%3Eabstain%20on%20this%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Indian%20representative%20on%20July%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20vote%20is%20significant%20as%20it%20is%20a%20recurring%20resolution%20that%20China%20tables%20every%20other%20year%20in%20the%20Council%20since%202017.%20It%20is%20the%20first%20ever%20solo%20resolution%20authored%20by%20China%20in%20the%20UNHRC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20previously%20always%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Chinese-authored%20resolution%20when%20it%20was%20tabled%20in%202017%2C%202019%2C%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20tabled%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20India%20had%20in%20fact%20commended%20the%20Chinese%20for%20%E2%80%9Caccommodating%20different%20perspectives%20and%20presenting%20a%20balanced%20text%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20the%20resolution%20under%20consideration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmindiaun.gov.in%2Fpages%2FMjAwNg%2C%2C%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20adopted%20by%20consensus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%20had%20said%20at%20the%20UNHRC%20in%20July%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20India%20altered%20its%20stance%20in%20response%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20introduction%20of%20new%20language%20in%20the%20text%20this%20year.%20The%20modified%20draft%20resolution%20now%20incorporates%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Chigh-quality%20development%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fenglish.scio.gov.cn%2Fm%2Ftopnews%2F2021-08%2F03%2Fcontent_77670307.htm%5C%22%3Ea%20term%20promoted%20by%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20the%20oldest%20resolution%20in%20the%20UNHRC%20that%20China%20has%20drafted%20alone%2C%20it%20also%20introduced%20a%20second%20resolution%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cpromoting%20mutually%20beneficial%20cooperation%20in%20the%20field%20of%20human%20rights%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20in%202018.%20After%20India%20returned%20to%20the%20UNHRC%20following%20a%20break%2C%20it%20voted%20against%20this%20resolution%20when%20it%20was%20introduced%20in%202020%20and%202021%2C%20due%20to%20its%20more%20blatant%20references%20to%20President%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20phrases%20in%20the%20title%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20had%20not%20re-tabled%20the%20%E2%80%98mutually%20beneficial%E2%80%99%20cooperation%20resolutions%20at%20any%20of%20the%20sessions%20last%20year%20in%20the%20UNHRC%2C%20when%20it%20was%20largely%20pre-occupied%20over%20the%20draft%20resolution%20moved%20by%20the%20western%20countries%20on%20Xinjiang.%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fat-unhrc-india-abstains-on-resolution-on-xinjiang-rejected-by-slim-margin%5C%22%3Ehad%20abstained%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20draft%20resolution%20which%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20majority%20of%20countries%2C%20but%20later%20said%20that%20China%20should%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fhope-china-addresses-objectively-and-properly-india-on-human-rights-concerns-in-xinjiang%5C%22%3Eaddress%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20the%20human%20rights%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Funravelling-modi-posturing-democracy-human-rights%5C%22%3EThe%20Unravelling%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Posturing%20on%20Democracy%20and%20Human%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9Cincremental%E2%80%99%20steps%20on%20AI%20and%20human%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNHRC%20adopted%20a%20resolution%20by%20consensus%20on%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments-dds-ny.un.org%2Fdoc%2FUNDOC%2FLTD%2FG23%2F140%2F62%2FPDF%2FG2314062.pdf%3FOpenElement%5C%22%3Enew%20and%20emerging%20digital%20technologies%20and%20human%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20take%20a%20rights-based%20approach%20into%20the%20field%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20China%20disassociated%20from%20the%20entire%20resolution%20but%20did%20not%20ask%20for%20a%20vote%2C%20India%20specifically%20disagreed%20and%20disassociated%20with%20a%20substantial%20paragraph%20that%20gave%20a%20number%20of%20directions%20on%20protecting%20vulnerable%20groups%20from%20use%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20various%20issues%20highlighted%20in%20the%20resolution%E2%80%99s%20operative%20paragraph%20(OP)%203%20was%20that%20data%20for%20AI%20systems%20are%20used%20in%20ways%20that%20are%20consistent%20with%20member%20state%E2%80%99s%20obligations%20under%20the%20international%20human%20rights%20law.%20It%20further%20called%20for%20ensuring%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20so%20that%20the%20use%20of%20AI%20systems%20does%20not%20lead%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20disinformation%20and%20hate%20speech%20%E2%80%93%20and%20ensure%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20especially%20if%20deployed%20to%20support%20content%20moderation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resolution%20also%20called%20in%20OP6%20for%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20Human%20Rights%20(OHCHR)%20to%20expand%20its%20capacities%20to%20advance%20human%20rights%20in%20the%20context%20of%20new%20and%20emerging%20technologies%2C%20including%20AI%20and%20to%20aid%20member%20states%20upon%20their%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20OP3%20has%20%E2%80%9Cnon-consensual%20language%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20said%20that%20the%20ambitious%20expansion%20of%20capacity%20of%20the%20OHCHR%20envisioned%20in%20OP6%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20curtail%20its%20functions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20diplomat%20expressed%20disappointment%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20request%20to%20%E2%80%9Cto%20take%20an%20incremental%20approach%20to%20the%20resolution%E2%80%99s%20outcomes%20could%20not%20be%20fully%20accommodated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20reasons%20mentioned%20before%2C%20we%20are%20constrained%20to%20dissociate%20from%20OP3.%20However%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20importance%20we%20attach%20to%20the%20subject%20of%20this%20resolution%2C%20we%20will%20join%20consensus%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmindiaun.gov.in%2Fpageinfo%2FMzAxNw%2C%2C%5C%22%3Eshe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECountry-specific%20resolutions%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%20six%20country-specific%20resolutions%2C%20India%20has%20abstained%20on%20the%20resolutions%20adopted%20related%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.1%2FResult%2520of%2520the%2520vote.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUkraine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.16%2FResult%2520of%2520the%2520vote.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESyria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.20%2FResult%2520of%2520the%2520vote.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBelarus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20it%20has%20done%20consistently%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lone%20negative%20vote%20from%20India%20during%20the%20entire%20session%20was%20on%20the%20resolution%20which%20extended%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20Special%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20human%20rights%20situation%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.21%2FResult%2520of%2520the%2520vote.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEritrea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20strategically%20located%20country%20in%20the%20Horn%20of%20Africa.%20India%20has%20been%20voting%20against%20resolutions%20on%20Eritrea%20since%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resolutions%20in%20the%20UNHRC%20sessions%2C%20prior%20to%202019%2C%20pertaining%20to%20Eritrea%20had%20been%20unanimously%20adopted%20as%20they%20were%20sponsored%20by%20the%20African%20group%2C%20including%20the%20resolution%20to%20establish%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20Special%20Rapporteur%20in%202012.%20Following%20Eritrea%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fethiopia-eritrea-restore-diplomatic-relations-1.4738578%5C%22%3Eimproved%20relations%20with%20Ethiopia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20African%20group%20subsequently%20withdrew%20its%20consent.%20However%2C%20starting%20in%202019%2C%20European%20countries%20began%20to%20table%20the%20resolution%20which%20led%20Eritrea%20and%20the%20African%20countries%20to%20rally%20votes%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.24_Rev.1%2FVoting%2520results.pdf%5C%22%3EIndia%20voted%20%E2%80%98yes%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20resolution%20that%20called%20on%20the%20UN%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20human%20rights%20to%20produce%20database%20of%20all%20companies%20operating%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.24_Rev.1%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsraeli%20settlements%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20resolution%20garnered%20support%20from%2031%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20who%20voted%20in%20favour.%20Thirteen%20countries%20chose%20to%20abstain%2C%20while%20only%20three%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20Czechia%20%E2%80%93%20voted%20against%20the%20resolution.%20It%20called%20for%20full%20implementation%20of%20the%20database%2C%20as%20per%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20resolution%2031%2F36%20adopted%20in%202016%2C%20for%20which%20India%20had%20also%20voted%20affirmatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20voted%20against%20the%20Eritrea%20resolution%2C%20it%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.25_Rev.1%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EColombia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20was%20sponsored%20by%20the%20South%20American%20country%20itself.%20As%20per%20the%20resolution%2C%20the%20commissioner%20has%20to%20appoint%20an%20international%20human%20rights%20expert%20immediately%20to%20identify%20the%20obstacles%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%202016%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20before%20the%20resolution%20was%20passed%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOrganisation%20of%20Islamic%20Cooperation%20(OIC)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20had%20introduced%20an%20amendment%20that%20sought%20to%20remove%20the%20language%20on%20violence%20against%20%E2%80%9Cpersons%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%E2%80%9D%20with%20%E2%80%9Cpersons%20in%20other%20vulnerable%20situations%E2%80%9D.%20Despite%20the%20decriminalisation%20of%20homosexuality%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.25_Rev.1%2FResult%2520of%2520vote%2520on%2520oral%2520amendment%25201.pdf%5C%22%3EIndia%20abstained%20on%20the%20amendment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20narrowly%20defeated%20due%20to%20combined%20votes%20of%20the%20European%20and%20Latin%20American%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20support%20of%20OIC-sponsored%20resolutions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20session%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20two%20resolutions%20brought%20by%20Pakistan%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20OIC%20group.%20One%20was%20the%20resolution%20on%20implementing%20the%20database%20for%20firms%20active%20in%20Israeli%20settlements%2C%20while%20the%20second%20one%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-unhrc-sweden-quran-burning%5C%22%3Eresolution%20against%20religious%20hatred%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20light%20of%20the%20Quran%20in%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20did%20not%20give%20an%20explanation%20of%20its%20vote%2C%20it%20had%20taken%20part%20in%20the%20Urgent%20Debate%20called%20in%20the%20Council%20on%20July%2011.%20While%20stating%20that%20the%20Council%20had%20to%20take%20account%20of%20%E2%80%9Cphobias%E2%80%9D%20against%20%E2%80%9Call%20religions%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20had%20not%20directly%20referred%20to%20the%20Swedish%20incident%20in%20its%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20taken%20an%20antagonistic%20position%20publicly%20against%20the%20OIC%2C%20which%20has%20criticised%20New%20Delhi%20for%20not%20taking%20action%20to%20stop%20violation%20of%20human%20rights%20of%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20in%20the%20now%20trifurcated%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-human-rights-record-un-upr-process-breakdown%5C%22%3EWho%20Said%20What%20at%20Evaluation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Human%20Rights%20Record%3A%20A%20Comprehensive%20Look%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolarisation%20on%20women%20and%20children%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20OIC%20and%20Russia%20targeted%20two%20resolutions%20related%20to%20women%20and%20girls%20with%20numerous%20amendments.%20None%20of%20the%20amendments%20were%20approved%2C%20but%20India%20voted%20either%20in%20favour%20of%20them%20or%20abstained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20three%20amendments%20introduced%20after%20the%20tabling%20of%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.5_Rev.1%2FEnglish_2.docx%5C%22%3Edraft%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20accelerating%20efforts%20to%20eliminate%20all%20forms%20of%20violence%20against%20women%20and%20girls%20in%20criminal%20justice%20detention.%20While%20it%20abstained%20on%20two%20of%20them%2C%20India%20voted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.33%2FResult%2520of%2520the%2520vote.pdf%5C%22%3Eyes%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.33%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20amendment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20the%20amendments%20were%20defeated%2C%20the%20draft%20resolution%20was%20adopted%20by%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20even%20more%20contentious%20hostile%20amendments%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.3_Rev.1%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3Edraft%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20ending%20child%2C%20early%20and%20forced%20marriages%2C%20which%20was%20sponsored%20by%20a%20cross-regional%20group%20of%20countries.%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20three%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20one%20was%20to%20align%20the%20draft%20to%20the%20UNGA%20outcomes%2C%20the%20other%20two%20amendments%20were%20to%20substantially%20modify%20the%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENigeria%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20sought%20to%20add%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.31%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3Eappropriate%20direction%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20from%20parents%20had%20to%20be%20sought%20with%20regard%20to%20sexual%20health%20of%20girls%20and%20boys.%20Egypt%20also%20introduced%20additional%20language%20to%20clarify%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrcmeetings.ohchr.org%2FHRCSessions%2FRegularSessions%2F53%2FDL_Resolutions%2FA_HRC_53_L.41%2FEnglish_1.docx%5C%22%3Edomestic%20and%20intimate%20partner%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20had%20to%20be%20addressed%2C%20as%20per%20national%20legal%20systems.%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20both%20of%20them%2C%20but%20all%20the%20amendments%20were%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20pointed%20out%20that%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20amendment%20as%20marital%20rape%20is%20not%20recognised%20under%20Indian%20jurisprudence.%20The%20unamended%20draft%20resolution%20was%20also%20adopted%20without%20a%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689665430000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffrom-china-to-ai-how-india-voted-at-the-uns-human-rights-body%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Out%20of%20the%20ten%20UNHRC%20resolutions%20that%20were%20put%20to%20a%20ballot%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20five%20times%2C%20abstained%20four%20times%2C%20and%20opposed%20one%20resolution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffrom-china-to-ai-how-india-voted-at-the-uns-human-rights-body%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20province%20saw%20cremations%20jump%20during%20Covid%20surge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689665386000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101851954%2Cimgsize-223928.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinese-province-saw-cremations-jump-during-covid-surge%2Farticleshow%2F101851963.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101851963.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinese-province-saw-cremations-jump-during-covid-surge%2Farticleshow%2F101851963.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinese-province-saw-cremations-jump-during-covid-surge%2Famp_art